<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00063</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE RIGHT OF CITIZENS TO INFORMATION HELD BY THE GOVERNMENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Peopleâ€™s Freedom Of Information Act</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to implement the right of the people to information on matters of public concern guaranteed in the aforementioned provision of the Constitution as well as adopting the policy of full public disclosure of all transactions in the government involving public interest, and; seeks to deter employees and officials of the government in entering into clandestine and often onerous transactions which debilitate the integrity of the governmental institutions they work for.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NOGRALES, KARLO ALEXEI B., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sambar (009 2016-08-10)</td><td>2. Panotes (034 2016-10-10)</td><tr><td>3. Gatchalian (057 2017-01-16)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC INFORMATION ON 2016-07-26</td></tr></table>